{"nodes": [{"id": "claude_md_project_instructions", "label": "CLAUDE.md Project Instructions", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Comprehensive developer reference documenting architecture, parser registry (25 parsers, 47+ companies), config keys, pipeline flow, and troubleshooting. Serves as the canonical source for adding new company crawlers."}, {"id": "concept_parser_registry", "label": "Parser Registry (25 parsers)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "CLAUDE.md", "source_location": "line 64", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Central registry mapping parser names to platform-specific scraping implementations. Split into 10 reusable platform parsers (workday, phenom, eightfold, jibe, radancy, greenhouse, greenhouse_api, oracle_hcm, avature, generic) and 15 company-specific parsers."}, {"id": "concept_pipeline_flow", "label": "Crawler Pipeline Flow", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "CLAUDE.md", "source_location": "line 122", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "_crawl_site() -> fetch_and_parse() -> filter_by_keywords() -> target_locations filter -> storage.add_jobs(). crawl_once() runs all sites in parallel via ThreadPoolExecutor. Interim email sent if slow sites timeout while fast ones find new jobs."}, {"id": "concept_workday_platform", "label": "Workday ATS Platform", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "CLAUDE.md", "source_location": "line 69", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Most common ATS platform in the registry. API pattern: POST to /wday/cxs/{co}/{SiteID}/jobs. Finding the site ID is the hardest part. applied_facets are site-specific (US country ID works for some but causes 400 on others)."}, {"id": "concept_greenhouse_api_platform",